&lt;h2 id="building-transit-networks"&gt;Building Transit Networks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can a cell learn? When a part of the plasmodium touches something attractive, e.g. food, it pulses more quickly and widens. If a part meets something repulsive, like light, it pulses more slowly and shrinks.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>